case:creator: SmartRPA by marco2012
concept:name: selectText
tag_value:
This paper proposes a novel approach for discovering routines distributed over time and people in UI logs leveraging time series mining.
Time series analysis offers a promising solution to address the limitations of existing approaches. 
UI logs themselves can be seen as a form of time series data, where user actions represent data points ordered chronologically. 
By employing time series mining techniques, we can uncover recurring patterns, i.e., so called time series motifs (\cite{Yeh.2017}), within the user interaction data.

tag_value:
To validate the effectiveness of our proposed approach for routine discovery, we generated a set of sample invoices. 
These invoices were sent to a designated team member on a regular basis while their actions were recorded for research purposes. 
The individual performed the simulated accounts payable process using a demo banking system, essentially executing an artificial transaction for each invoice received. 
The recording process was facilitated by two software tools: SmartRPA\cite{Agostinelli.2021d} and Tockler.\footnote{Tockler: \url{https://maygo.github.io/tockler/}} 
This dual recording approach allows us to analyze routine discovery from two distinct log data sources in Section \ref{sec:evaluation}.
The logs from the recording sessions are available with the artifact in the repository.
